EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to veterans; requiring the Director of the
Department of Veterans Services to develop and make
available to certain agencies, resource centers or programs
a program of training and informational materials
concerning the process for applying for an upgrade to the
character of a veteran’s discharge from service or a
change in the narrative reason for a veteran’s discharge
from service; and providing other matters properly
relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires the Director of the Department of Veterans Services to
2 conduct outreach to, and provide assistance designed for the unique needs of, veterans
3 and members of the military who are lesbian, gay, bisexual or transgender and their
4 spouses and dependents. Existing law further requires this outreach and assistance to
5 include, without limitation, a requirement for the Director to provide assistance in
6 applying for an upgrade to the character of the veteran’s discharge from service or a
7 change in the narrative reason for the veteran’s discharge from service. (NRS
8 417.121) This bill additionally requires the Director to, as part of such outreach and
9 assistance, develop and make available to any agency, resource center or program in
10 this State which provides services and resources to veterans and members of the
11 military regarding the benefits, services, programs and assistance available to veterans
12 a program of training and informational materials concerning the process for applying
13 for an upgrade to the character of the veteran’s discharge from service or a change in
14 the narrative reason for the veteran’s discharge from service.
